PLAGUE, BUBONIC - MONGOLIA & CHINA: BACKGROUND
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Bubonic plague, marmots - Mongolia: RFI 2000.3050
Date: 1 Aug 2000 20:42:10 +0300
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON <http://www.cynifo.com>

The following background data on plague in Mongolia and China were
abstracted from GIDEON <http://www.cynifo.com>
China:
Most cases of plague occur in Tibet and Xinjiang. In recent years, new
natural foci have been identified in Inner Mongolia, Sichuan, Xizang and
Ynnan. 84 cases (50 fatal) were reported in Tibet during 1966 to 1994.
Year Cases in China Fatalities
1975-1979 18
1980 30 20
1981 1 0
1982 0 0
1983 25 15
1984 0 0
1985 6 2
1986 8 3
1987 7 2
1988 6 4
1989 10 6
1990 75 2
1991 29 11
1992 35 6
1993 13 1
1994 7 4
1995 8 0
1996 98* 7
*88 cases in Yunnan and 3 in Qinghai
64 cases were reported in Qinghai Province during 1975 to 1997 - 10 of
these acquired from infected Tibetan sheep.
43 cases of human plague (0 fatal) were reported in 1997 - 35 in 4 counties
of Yunnan Province and 8 in two counties of Qinghai province. The same
year, epizootics were reported in Gansu, Inner Mongolia, Qinghai, Sichuan,
Xinjiang, Xizang and Yunnan.
Mongolia:
Highest rates are registered during July to September, with recent
outbreaks reported in Uvs and Uvuhangai provinces. One case was reported in
1985; 5 (3 fatal) in 1989; 15 (5 fatal) in 1990. Three cases (0 fatal) were
reported in 1991; 12 (4 fatal) in 1992; 21 (7 fatal) in 1993 (from Khovd
Aimak, Uvurhangai Aimak, Hentii and Zavhan Aimak); 0 in 1994; 1 (fatal) in
1995 (Mankhan District of Khovd Aimak. One case (Jargalant District,
Gobi-Altai Province - nonfatal) was reported in August 1996; 4 (2 fatal) in
1997 - from Gobi-Altai and Uvurhangai Provinces; 207 (9 fatal) in 1998 -
from Khovd, Bayan-Ulgii and Arkangai Provinces. Four cases (1 fatal) were
reported from Arkhangai, Bayan-Ulgii, Khuvsgul and Khovd Provinces in 1999.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
